column5: Remebmer the agreement states that you have to buy a ticket to share in the winnings, did you get one before you left for DC?I hope so, no ticket, no 1/2 of pot to you!

I will be looking to purchase a nice cabin on a lake, which lake should I chose? I am thinking about the western Ontario area but cannot decide what lake is best. I've never been to Lac Seul but read alot on it. What about Eagle lake? I enjoy the Kenora area but Lake of the Woods is too big for my taste. My perfered prey is the walleye, but also love smack time with smalliesCan I even by a cabin if I am not a resident of Canada,,, I don't know?As you can see cabin fever has hit me hard!
Buy one on Lake of the Woods, let me know if you need a personal guide, Good Luck!
When you win the Lottery buy one on each...heck just buy your own Lake.
If it were me...Lac Seul, Rainy, or Minnitaki. I am definately buying a ticket tonight. I really don't want to go to work tomorrow.
Yes, you can buy a cabin if you're not a citizen. I'd also suggest LOTW's... but there's lots of small lakes in the area around nestor falls that you can find a very remote cabin.
Heck no! not even 2 numbers right, guess I;ll have to wait until the weekend when they draw again to start planning my cabin purchase
Tell him to hold it and when I win on Friday I will be calling.You can join me for the first fish fry weekend!
Got another chance at it tomorrow night, $212 million will buy a lot of minnows and Labby's for my new cabin
$106 million for you and $106 million for me. Now that I am out of pocket you plan on taking all the money for yourself? What about our agreement?
